'''Doug Gallagher''' (born ) is an American businessman and founder of Gallagher Financial Systems, a software company based in .
In , he announced his candidacy in the  to replace outgoing Sen. . A , he distanced himself from Republican social issues such as the  debate, instead focusing on economic issues such as taxation and . After a late start in the Republican race, July polling showed him in third place behind rivals  and , thanks in part to publicity generated by his pro-business, anti-lawyer message. Gallagher gained some attention during the race for producing a film short, "The Great Florida Picture Show," which his campaign burned onto s and mailed to 400,000 Floridian voters. He was defeated by Martinez in the  on .